bcl:definition.bcl:text:
restricted constitution means a constitution of a corporation that
restricts the corporation to investing only in equity shares of a particular eligible
business and affiliates of that eligible business;

subsidiary means a corporation that, in respect of another
corporation, is controlled, either directly or indirectly, by that other
corporation;

bcl:paragraph.bcl:text:
